    "result": {"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h3 id=\"a-nice-terminal-experience-starts-with-the-shell\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#a-nice-terminal-experience-starts-with-the-shell\" aria-label=\"a nice terminal experience starts with the shell permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>A nice terminal experience starts with the shell</h3>\n<p>We don't need to spend a lot of time here.  There are a ton of options, again,\nbut this time I will make a strong suggestion.</p>\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<h3 id=\"strongly-suggest-zsh\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#strongly-suggest-zsh\" aria-label=\"strongly suggest zsh permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Strongly suggest zsh</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>its default on mac, something at least they have done right</li>\n<li>its easy to install on ubuntu</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">sudo apt install zsh\nchsh -s $(which zsh)</code></pre></div>\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<h3 id=\"but-what-is-a-shell\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#but-what-is-a-shell\" aria-label=\"but what is a shell permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>But what is a shell?</h3>\n<p>The <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/user/lastmiles\">Wizard</a> explained the shell once\nto me in the following way.  He gets banned from twitch regularly, so..... that\nlink is to his youtube.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\"># you meant ls -la\nls -;a</code></pre></div>\n<ul>\n<li>Don't forget to draw :)</li>\n<li>Do the <code class=\"language-text\">ps -o pid,ppid= -C zsh</code> example</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"terminal-vs-shell\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#terminal-vs-shell\" aria-label=\"terminal vs shell permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Terminal vs Shell</h3>\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<h3 id=\"shell-can-be-great\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#shell-can-be-great\" aria-label=\"shell can be great permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Shell can be great</h3>\n<p>A lot of point counter point talk on the internet for bash vs zsh vs tsh vs bsh\nvs fish</p>\n<ul>\n<li>I am just going to give you what I like</li>\n</ul>\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<h3 id=\"ohmyzsh\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#ohmyzsh\" aria-label=\"ohmyzsh permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>OhMyZsh</h3>\n<p>YES I ADMIT IT.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>How to install</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">curl -L https://raw.github.com/robbyrussell/oh-my-zsh/master/tools/install.sh | sh</code></pre></div>\n<p>So what do I get out of oh-my-zsh?</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Open up .zshrc and go to lines plugins</li>\n</ul>\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<h3 id=\"personal-opinion\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#personal-opinion\" aria-label=\"personal opinion permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Personal Opinion</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Choose something</li>\n<li>Learn about it to some small amount</li>\n<li>Get good at core utils</li>\n<li>Take advantage of already built tools that are amazing.</li>\n</ul>\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<h3 id=\"apply-what-you-have-learned\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#apply-what-you-have-learned\" aria-label=\"apply what you have learned permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Apply what you have learned</h3>\n<p>Lets say you decide, yes I want zsh and oh my zsh.  What should you do?</p>\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<p>PUT IT IN YOUR ANSIBLE</p>\n<h4 id=\"fun-side-note\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#fun-side-note\" aria-label=\"fun side note permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Fun side note</h4>\n<p>I actually forgot to do it for myself and so when I originally executed this I\ndidn't have zsh-autosuggestions installed.  Took a moment to figure it out.</p>\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />","frontmatter":{"path":"/shell","title":"Your shell","order":"30A","section":"CLI - Beginning"}},"allMarkdownRemark":{"edges":[{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"8A","path":"/ansible-as-a-workstation","title":"Ansible"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"37A","path":"/cht.sh","title":"Syntax..."}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"12A","path":"/dotfile-system-setup-summary","title":"Dotfile and System Setup Summary"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"11A","path":"/dotfile-management","title":"Dotfile Management!"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"35A","path":"/fzf","title":"FZF"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"50A","path":"/git","title":"Git - The cool parts"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"4A","path":"/here-we-go","title":"Here we go!"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"3A","path":"/inspiration","title":"Inspiration - Why Dev workflow"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"2A","path":"/intro-2","title":"Introduction: Life as a developer"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"1A","path":"/intro","title":"Introduc